## Overview of the License

The GNU Affero General Public License (AGPL) ensures that this software remains free and open-source, even when used in networked applications. Below is a summary of what this license allows and requires.

### Permissions

You are free to:
- Use the software for any purpose, including commercial use
- Modify and enhance the source code
- Contribute improvements back to the project
- Distribute copies of the software
- Build applications that incorporate this software

### Requirements

If you use this software, you **must**:
- Retain the GNU AGPL v3 (or later) license for any modifications
- Open-source your entire project that uses this software
- Provide the source code to anyone who uses your software
- Share any improvements back to the community

### Key Protection

The AGPL prevents anyone from using this software to create proprietary or closed-source products. All derivative works must remain open-source and freely available.

## Network Copyleft Provision

If you run this software on a server and provide it as a service over a network, you **must** make the source code available to all users of that service, ensuring transparency and compliance with the AGPL.

